dcterms:description: CIFAR-10 is a well-known benchmark in computer vision and deep learning, consisting of 60,000 images divided into ten distinct classes, each containing 6,000 images of size 32x32. The dataset is split into a training set with 50,000 images and a test set with 10,000 images.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-10

dcterms:description: JFT-300M is a large-scale dataset used for training vision transformers, consisting of 300 million labeled images. It is designed to facilitate the training of models that require substantial amounts of data.
dcterms:title: JFT-300M

dcterms:description: ImageNet is a large visual database designed for use in visual object recognition software research. It contains millions of images labeled with thousands of categories.
dcterms:title: ImageNet

dcterms:description: Tf-flowers is a dataset containing images of flowers, used for training models in image classification tasks.
